The paper deals with the problem of centralized coded caching, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses a placement strategy that can be applied to an arbitrary number of users and files, which involves data structures (cs.DS). The proposed strategy also takes into account non-uniform demands and user-specific file popularities, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networked information (cs.NI). Finally, the paper establishes the optimal expected memory-rate trade-off for the case of two files, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.CC).
